</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9C2C3078B6EFFE9FE5DFAB6FE786F07" bold="true" box="[451,502,1335,1359]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2F17E7C8B6EFFE9FE5DFAB6FE786F07" box="[451,502,1335,1359]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Deeming. Female.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B091F158B6EFFE9FF59FAFDFE136FF3" blockId="26.[151,1437,1404,2044]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="B9C2C3078B6EFFE9FF59FAFDFE866FDF" bold="true" box="[199,264,1404,1431]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="138D03908B6EFFE9FE89FAFCFEE06FD0" box="[279,366,1405,1432]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1918,1943]" captionTargetBox="[162,1435,887,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,885,1893]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 26. Kwarea ismayi. a) Head in profile. (iv) denotes inner vertical seta, (ov) outer vertical seta, (po) postocellar and (oc) ocellar; b) Middle third of length of male mid femur in dorsal aspect. (A) denotes anterior, (B) basal, (Ap) apical and (MP) mid point of length; c) Wing; d) Male genitalia from beneath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3895917" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3895917/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig 26c</figureCitation>
) with an even distribution of microchaetae, except on cell basad of humeral crossvein, which is largely devoid of them.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B091F158B6EFFE9FF59FA45FC136FA8" blockId="26.[151,1437,1404,2044]" box="[199,925,1476,1504]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="B9C2C3078B6EFFE9FF59FA45FEB26F97" bold="true" box="[199,316,1476,1503]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Abdomen</emphasis>
Sternites weakly developed. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="138D03908B6EFFE9FCABFA44FC1E6FA8" box="[821,912,1477,1504]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1918,1943]" captionTargetBox="[162,1435,887,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,885,1893]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 26. Kwarea ismayi. a) Head in profile. (iv) denotes inner vertical seta, (ov) outer vertical seta, (po) postocellar and (oc) ocellar; b) Middle third of length of male mid femur in dorsal aspect. (A) denotes anterior, (B) basal, (Ap) apical and (MP) mid point of length; c) Wing; d) Male genitalia from beneath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3895917" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3895917/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig 26d</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B091F158B6EFFE9FF59FA68FC546C4B" blockId="26.[151,1437,1404,2044]" box="[199,986,1513,1540]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="B9C2C3078B6EFFE9FF59FA68FE936C4B" bold="true" box="[199,285,1513,1539]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Length</emphasis>
. 1.0 mm, of wing 1.0mm, of female sometimes slightly larger.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3AC4C9E8B6EFFE9FF59F98CFBCF6DB3" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B091F158B6EFFE9FF59F98CFBCF6DB3" blockId="26.[151,1437,1404,2044]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="B9C2C3078B6EFFE9FF59F98CFEBA6C6F" bold="true" box="[199,308,1549,1575]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Remarks</emphasis>
. Um Al-Raq Island is situated in the Farasan Island group in the Red Sea. Being inhabited only by a Saudi Arabian Army unit responsible for security, it is almost totally undisturbed, and no agricultural activity occurs there. The soldiers being persistently heavily bitten by a 
<taxonomicName id="4CB664968B6EFFE9FC8FF9D7FC2E6C27" authorityName="Skuse" authorityYear="1889" box="[785,928,1622,1647]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Leptoconops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9C2C3078B6EFFE9FC8FF9D7FC2E6C27" box="[785,928,1622,1647]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Leptoconops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. (
<taxonomicName id="4CB664968B6EFFE9FC48F9D4FB126C38" authorityName="Newman" authorityYear="1834" box="[982,1180,1621,1648]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ceratopogonidae</taxonomicName>
), one of us (HAD) visited the island to look into control measures for the pest. In sweeping, sticky and Malaise trapping several dipterous species not previously found on the largest of the Farasan Islands were found to be abundant. Amongst these was a new species of 
<taxonomicName id="4CB664968B6EFFE9FEC9F943FDEB6C93" authority="Sabrosky, 1954" authorityName="Sabrosky" authorityYear="1954" box="[343,613,1728,1755]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Kwarea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9C2C3078B6EFFE9FEC9F943FE216C93" box="[343,431,1730,1755]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Kwarea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF2762E48B6EFFE9FE28F940FDEB6C93" author="Sabrosky, C. W." box="[438,613,1728,1755]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="36 - 46" refId="ref29764" refString="Sabrosky, C. W. (1954) Some East African Diptera of the families Acroceridae, Asteiidae and Chloropidae. Bulletin of the Brooklyn Entomological Society 49 (2), 36 - 46." type="journal article" year="1954">Sabrosky, 1954</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which genus was previously known only from the generotype species 
<taxonomicName id="4CB664968B6EFFE9FA1DF943FE466CB7" authority="Sabrosky, 1954" authorityName="Sabrosky" authorityYear="1954" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Kwarea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidihirta">
<emphasis id="B9C2C3078B6EFFE9FA1DF943FE996CB7" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">K. pallidihirta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF2762E48B6EFFE9FE83F964FE466CB7" author="Sabrosky, C. W." box="[285,456,1764,1791]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="36 - 46" refId="ref29764" refString="Sabrosky, C. W. (1954) Some East African Diptera of the families Acroceridae, Asteiidae and Chloropidae. Bulletin of the Brooklyn Entomological Society 49 (2), 36 - 46." type="journal article" year="1954">Sabrosky, 1954</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F3A15F858B6EFFE9FD94F964FDFC6CB7" box="[522,626,1765,1791]" name="Tanzania" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
. Of this species only the 
<typeStatus id="540DA1B78B6EFFE9FC1AF964FC686CB7" box="[900,998,1765,1791]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="540DA1B78B6EFFE9FB84F967FBF46D48" box="[1050,1146,1766,1792]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">paratype</typeStatus>
(both of which are males) are recorded. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF2762E48B6EFFE9FEACF888FD966D6B" author="Sabrosky, C. W." box="[306,536,1800,1827]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="36 - 46" refId="ref29764" refString="Sabrosky, C. W. (1954) Some East African Diptera of the families Acroceridae, Asteiidae and Chloropidae. Bulletin of the Brooklyn Entomological Society 49 (2), 36 - 46." type="journal article" year="1954">Sabrosky (1954: 45)</bibRefCitation>
likens 
<taxonomicName id="4CB664968B6EFFE9FDF5F88BFD4D6D6B" authorityName="Sabrosky" authorityYear="1954" box="[619,707,1802,1827]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Kwarea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9C2C3078B6EFFE9FDF5F88BFD4D6D6B" box="[619,707,1802,1827]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Kwarea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4CB664968B6EFFE9FD76F888FC3A6D6B" authority="Becker" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1912" box="[744,948,1801,1827]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Psilacrum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9C2C3078B6EFFE9FD76F888FCD56D6B" box="[744,859,1801,1827]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Psilacrum</emphasis>
Becker
</taxonomicName>
, both having proclinate ocellar setae, but it differs from that genus in the development of the orbital setae, which are erect, strongly developed and three in number, rather than weak, and in having the postocellar (as postvertical) setae parallel to one another, rather than cruciate. He provides a modification to his (1951) key to the genera of 
<taxonomicName id="4CB664968B6EFFE9FCF3F8F4FC776DC7" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1910" box="[877,1017,1909,1935]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Oscinellinae">Oscinellinae</taxonomicName>
of the Ethiopian region (pp.743–747) to accommodate 
<taxonomicName id="4CB664968B6EFFE9FEC6F81BFE3E6DFB" authorityName="Sabrosky" authorityYear="1954" box="[344,432,1946,1971]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Kwarea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9C2C3078B6EFFE9FEC6F81BFE3E6DFB" box="[344,432,1946,1971]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Kwarea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Since the number of erect strong orbital bristles differs in the two species between three and four, the generic diagnosis must be modified to take this into account. No mention of either 
<taxonomicName id="4CB664968B6EFFE9FB45F83FFABD6D9F" authorityName="Sabrosky" authorityYear="1954" box="[1243,1331,1982,2007]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Kwarea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9C2C3078B6EFFE9FB45F83FFABD6D9F" box="[1243,1331,1982,2007]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Kwarea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4CB664968B6EFFE9FAC7F83CFF5F6DB3" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Psilacrum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9C2C3078B6EFFE9FAC7F83CFF5F6DB3" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Psilacrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF2762E48B6EFFE9FED1F860FDA56DB3" author="Andersson, H." box="[335,555,2017,2043]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 200" refId="ref26990" refString="Andersson, H. (1977) Taxonomic and phylogenetic studies on Chloropidae (Diptera) with special reference to Old World genera. Entomologica Scandinavica Supplement 8, 1 - 200. Lund." type="journal article" year="1977">Andersson’s (1977)</bibRefCitation>
treatment of Old World genera of 
<taxonomicName id="4CB664968B6EFFE9FC30F860FBB26DB3" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[942,1084,2017,2043]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chloropidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3AC4C9E8B6FFFE8FF59FF18FCF76B0B" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B091F158B6FFFE8FF59FF18FAE56AB2" blockId="27.[151,1436,152,251]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="B9C2C3078B6FFFE8FF59FF18FEC06AFB" bold="true" box="[199,334,153,179]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Etymology.</emphasis>
Dr. John Ismay has prepared figures of the whole insect, frons and genitalia of one of the two specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4CB664968B6FFFE8FF69FF3CFE196A9E" authorityName="Sabrosky" authorityYear="1954" box="[247,407,188,214]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Kwarea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidihirta">
<emphasis id="B9C2C3078B6FFFE8FF69FF3CFE196A9E" box="[247,407,188,214]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">K. pallidihirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and has very kindly given us copies of these, which greatly enhance the rather brief original description, and serve to differentiate the two species. In gratitude for this the new species is dedicated to him.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B091F158B6FFFE8FF09FEA9FCF76B0B" blockId="27.[151,889,296,323]" box="[151,889,296,323]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
This species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4CB664968B6FFFE8FE2BFEA8FDDB6B0A" authorityName="Sabrosky" authorityYear="1954" box="[437,597,296,322]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Kwarea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidihirta">
<emphasis id="B9C2C3078B6FFFE8FE2BFEA8FDDB6B0A" box="[437,597,296,322]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">K. pallidihirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the following respects:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
